Sonex Research Inc said itsmodified 1986 British Ford Escort passed the European emissionstest, but reported the engine consumed 35 pct more fuel thanthe stock engine.    Sonex said its engine is not equipped with a catalyticconverter and does not use exhaust gas recirculation or anemission air pump. It said the company expected to realize areduced fuel economy, but is working on improving fuelconsumption.    The company said after it installs the new fuel system, itwill retest the automobile.    In a separate announcement, the company said it receivedconfirmation from the European Patent Office that Sonexsuccessfully defended its BETA European Patent from acompetitor. Reuter&#3;